    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "How much? / How many? - شْحال؟"
        },
        "text": "The most common way to ask 'how much?' or 'how many?' in Darija is by using the word 'شْحال؟'. It's a versatile word used for both quantities and prices.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شْحال؟",
            "english": "How much (is it)? / How many?",
            "transliteration": "shHal?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شْحال هادي؟",
            "english": "How much is this?",
            "transliteration": "shHal hadi?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Basic Numbers 1-3"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn the first few numbers, which are essential when asking about quantities or giving simple counts.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "واحْد",
            "english": "One",
            "transliteration": "waHed"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "جُوج",
            "english": "Two",
            "transliteration": "juj"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "تْلاتَة",
            "english": "Three",
            "transliteration": "tlata"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How many X?' - شْحال من...؟"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'how many of something?' you combine 'شْحال' with 'من' (men) followed by the noun. This structure is common for inquiring about quantities of objects or people.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شْحال من كتاب؟",
            "english": "How many books?",
            "transliteration": "shHal men ktab?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شْحال من واحد؟",
            "english": "How many people?",
            "transliteration": "shHal men waHed?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "شْحال من كتاب عندك؟",
        "english": "How many books do you have?",
        "transliteration": "shHal men ktab 'andk?"
      },
      "context": "Asking about the quantity of books someone possesses."
    },
    {
